-- China Stocks Movers: China Shenhua, Jiangxi Copper, ICBC
-- B y   E e   C h i e n   C h u a
-- 2012-06-21T08:42:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-21/china-stocks-movers-china-shenhua-jiangxi-copper-icbc.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses as of the close.  The  Shanghai Composite Index (SHCOMP) , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, dropped 1.4 percent to 2,260.88, the
lowest close since March 29. The  CSI 300 Index (SHSZ300)  fell 1.6 percent
to 2,512.19, the lowest close for the gauge since April 9.
Financial markets are closed tomorrow for a holiday.  Commodities:  Jiangxi Copper Co. (600362)  (600362 CH), China’s
biggest copper producer, fell 3 percent to 24.48 yuan, the most
since June 4.  China Shenhua Energy Co. (601088)  (601088 CH), the
country’s largest coal producer, slid 2.3 percent to 23.38 yuan,
the lowest close since Jan. 28, 2011. The stocks declined on
concern that demand for commodities will slow.  Industrial & Commercial Bank of China Ltd.  (601398 CH)
dropped 0.8 percent to 3.91  yuan , the lowest close since Sept.
20, 2010. The bank paced a retreat for lenders after the 21st
Century Business Herald said the four biggest banks saw net
deposits decline by a combined 460 billion yuan ($72 billion) in
the first two weeks of this month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
